    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix RLC UM reception actions for out-of-order PDU handling\n\n### Summary\nThe `rlc_um_reception_actions` function in `rlc_entity_um.c` was not correctly handling PDUs received outside the reception window. This caused issues with sequence number management and reassembly timing.\n\n### Changes\n- `openair2/LAYER2/rlc_v2/rlc_entity_um.c`: Modified the reception actions logic to properly check SN against VR(UH) before updating window parameters\n- Added proper conditional handling for PDUs within vs outside reception window\n- Improved comment documentation to match 3GPP TS 36.322 specification\n\n### Reproduction\nUnder certain network conditions with packet loss and reordering, the RLC UM entity would incorrectly advance VR(UH) when receiving PDUs with SN < VR(UH) but outside the current reception window. This led to:\n- Premature release of buffered PDUs\n- Incorrect sequence number tracking\n- Potential data loss in reassembled SDUs\n\nThe issue manifests as intermittent RLC reassembly failures during handover procedures and high packet loss scenarios.\n"
}